To retrieve content files on Shopify using the REST API, you can use the `GET /admin/api/2021-07/themes/{theme_id}/assets.json` endpoint. This endpoint allows you to get all the assets (including content files) in a theme.

To get the image files associated with the content files, you would need to examine the contents of the asset. If the content file is an HTML file with an `img` tag, for example, you can extract the `src` attribute of that tag to get the URL of the associated image.

Here's an example of how to retrieve content files and associated images using the Shopify API in JavaScript:

```javascript
const shopifyApiUrl = 'https://{store-name}.myshopify.com/admin/api/2021-07';

// Replace {store-name} with the name of your Shopify store.

const fetchContentFilesAndImages = async (themeId) => {
  const assetsResponse = await fetch(`${shopifyApiUrl}/themes/${themeId}/assets.json`);
  const assets = await assetsResponse.json();

  const contentFiles = Object.entries(assets).filter(([filename, asset]) => 
    asset.content_type === 'text/html' && filename.startsWith('templates/')
  );

  const images = contentFiles.flatMap(([filename, asset]) => {
    const content = asset.value;
    const imgRegex = /<img.+?src="(.+?)"/g;
    const matches = [...content.matchAll(imgRegex)];
    return matches.map(([, imageUrl]) => imageUrl);
  });

  return { contentFiles, images };
};

// Example usage:
fetchContentFilesAndImages(1234567890)
  .then(({ contentFiles, images }) => {
    console.log('Content files:', contentFiles);
    console.log('Images:', images);
  })
  .catch((error) => {
    console.error(error);
  });
```

In this example, the `fetchContentFilesAndImages` function retrieves all assets from the given theme ID, filters them to include only the HTML files in the `templates` directory, and then extracts the URLs of any images referenced in those HTML files. The function returns an object with two properties: `contentFiles` (an array of `[filename, asset]` pairs for each content file) and `images` (an array of image URLs). You can modify this function to suit your specific needs for retrieving content files and associated images.
